how do i use my web client tags in outlook stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how do i use my web client tags in outlook categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how do i use my web client tags in outlook search this site tags are your personal classification system for email messages contacts tasks and appointments you can use outlook calendar to access all of the tags that you created in the web client in outlook tags are called categories to apply web client tags to your outlook calendar make sure that the outlook connector is installed right click on a appointment you want to tag and select categorize click to select the desired tag the appointment changes to the selected color to create rename or delete tags through your outlook calendar make sure that the outlook connector is installed right click on a appointment you want to tag and select all categories the color categories dialog box opens to create a new tag click new enter a name assign a color if desired and click ok to rename an existing tag select the tag and enter a new name to delete a tag select the tag click delete and click yes at the prompt click ok note there are more color options in outlook than in the web client so the color assigned to your category may appear as a different color in the web client for more information see the create and work with tags page watch a video helplet about creating and working with tags outlook at stanford stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
